# ── Ground-truth sample data — Karissa's private POS exports ──────
# Real salon data used for parser validation and format comparison.
# NEVER commit — contains PHI-adjacent business data, stylist names, revenue.
sample_data/
data/inbox/
data/archive/

# ── Inbox dedup ledger — INTENTIONALLY COMMITTED ─────────────
# data/processed_attachments.json is the SHA256 idempotency ledger for the
# Gmail attachment watcher. It MUST persist across GitHub Actions runs
# (ephemeral runners reset the filesystem every Monday), so we commit it.
# Contains only hashes, filenames, ISO timestamps, and Gmail message IDs —
# no PHI. The workflow's "Commit inbox ledger" step keeps it in sync.
# See INBOX_LEDGER_PERSISTENCE_DECISION.md for the rationale.
!data/processed_attachments.json
**/March */
**/Weekly Report*
**/Salon Summary*
**/Employee KPI*
**/FS Salon Dashboard*
.claude/scheduled_tasks.lock

# ── Weekly backfill report files — provided locally, NOT committed ───────────
# Tony downloads 12 salons × ~52 weeks of POS reports into
# backfill/weekly/{Zenoti,SU}/<YYYY-MM-DD>/ folders. Bulk inputs (reproducible
# by re-download, carry stylist names) — keep the repo lean. The loader, the
# bucket dirs (.gitkeep), and READMEs ARE committed. See BACKFILL_RUNBOOK.md.
# Date folders + .gitkeep ARE committed (so the empty structure syncs via git
# pull); only the report FILES dropped into them are ignored, by extension:
backfill/weekly/**/*.xls
backfill/weekly/**/*.xlsx
backfill/weekly/**/*.xlsm
backfill/weekly/**/*.pdf
backfill/weekly/**/*.csv
